# 📊 Bank Marketing Term Deposit Prediction

## 📌 Project Overview
This project predicts whether a bank customer will subscribe to a term deposit based on marketing campaign data.  
It uses machine learning models and explainable AI techniques to analyze customer behavior.

---

## 🎯 Objective
- Predict term deposit subscription (Yes/No)
- Compare classification models
- Evaluate performance using multiple metrics
- Explain predictions using SHAP (Explainable AI)

---

## 📂 Dataset
- Source: UCI Machine Learning Repository  
- Dataset: Bank Marketing Dataset  
- File: `bank-additional-full.csv`

---

## 🧠 Machine Learning Models Used
- Logistic Regression
- Random Forest Classifier

---

## ⚙️ Workflow

### 1. Data Preprocessing
- Handling categorical variables using Label Encoding
- Feature scaling using StandardScaler
- Train-test split (80/20)

### 2. Model Training
- Logistic Regression (baseline model)
- Random Forest (advanced model)

### 3. Evaluation Metrics
- Confusion Matrix
- F1 Score
- ROC Curve & AUC Score

### 4. Explainable AI (XAI)
- SHAP (SHapley Additive Explanations)
- Feature impact visualization
- Explanation of 5 individual predictions

---

## 📊 Results

| Model               | F1 Score | AUC Score |
|--------------------|----------|----------|
